The Olympic flame does not illuminate every event the same.
Further from the centre, partly in the shade are the sports that are not universally accepted: air gun shooting, archery, badminton, taekwondo.
We will always have the breast swimming and may it reign for a long time.
But if I might modestly make arguments for my particular darling, then let me draw attention to the trampoline's discreet charm.
Although trampoline jumping has been an Olympic event since 2000, when it made its debut in Sydney, it has been perceived so sparsely for the past 16 years that many who, I had interviewed, did not know that it is an Olympic sport at all.
This could also be regional ignorance.
